
    COMPANY DESCRIPTION

    Singapore Management University is a place where high-level professionalism blends together with a healthy informality. The 'family-like' atmosphere among the SMU community fosters a culture where employees work, plan, organise and play together &ndash; building a strong collegiality and morale within the university.Our commitment to attract and retain talent is ongoing. We offer attractive benefits and welfare, competitive compensation packages, and generous professional development opportunities &ndash; all to meet the work-life needs of our staff. No wonder, then, that SMU continues to be given numerous awards and recognition for its human resource excellence.

    RESPONSIBILITIES

    
Design and implement solutions that automatically harvests, links, and makes sense of information units about APIs from various media -- API documentations, posts in question and answer sites, GitHub repositories, programming videos on YouTube, software development related microblogs on Twitter, CVE vulnerability reports, etc. -- to make effective and explainable API recommendations using the power of deep neural networks.b)
Conduct evaluations and user studies to validate the effectiveness of the algorithms and toolsc)
Write and publish research papers and present them to reputable academic conferences)
Package the documents, implementation code, evaluate results of the project for public releasee)
Liaise with the overseas and industry collaborators of this project to realize the overall goal of the project

QUALIFICATIONS
    
Minimum PhD degree in Information Systems / Computer Science / Software Engineering
Strong relevant research capability as evidenced by at least 3 publications in top-tier software engineering conferences/journals
Deep knowledge about software engineering and deep learning research relevant to the project
Competent in designing and implementing algorithms and data
Highly fluent in Python and Java 
Good oral and written communication skills
Able to work both independently and as part of a team
Able to work under strict deadlines
Able to start work in the next few months


